TO START THIS APPLICATION

1. Open a terminal
2. Navigate to the host directory
3. Run the command: sudo ./start.sh  (You may be prompted to enter password or type Y and press Enter)
4. After completion, enter the following commands:
5. mysql> create database flaskapp; (First Time)
6. mysql> use flaskapp;
7. mysql> source flaskapp.sql; (First Time)
8. mysql> exit
9. sudo python3 -m flask run 
10. Open a new terminal without closing the first one, navigate to the host directory
11. run the command: python3 Consumer.py
12. Open a web browser and navigate to: http://127.0.0.1:5000/
